Package: extendrpolarsexamples
Title: Template Package Extending 'polars' Package with Rust.
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
  c(person("Soren", "Welling", , "sorhawell@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")))
Description:
  Use this tempplate package as a starting point to interface rust projects with the
  polars package. We strive for backward/forward version compatability.
  This package uses the rust crate extendr_polars to perform conversions.
  See `src/rust/src/lib.rs` for how to interface from rust.s
License: MIT + file LICENSE
SystemRequirements: Rust tool chain w/ cargo, libclang/llvm-config
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
Imports:
  polars (>= 0.7.0),
Suggests:
    rmarkdown,
    testthat  (>= 3.0.0),
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Config/rextendr/version: 0.3.1
